1
00:00:13,224 --> 00:00:16,185
- Do you have your boarding pass?
- Wait a sec.

2
00:00:19,105 --> 00:00:20,305
Thank you.

3
00:00:25,105 --> 00:00:28,345
One of my officers has noticed
your MO and travel pattern.

4
00:00:32,865 --> 00:00:34,665
What were your travel dates?

5
00:00:34,745 --> 00:00:36,545
That was your MO, not mine.

6
00:00:38,545 --> 00:00:40,465
- Where are you putting up?
- Novotel.

7
00:00:40,985 --> 00:00:42,585
I'll pick you up tonight.

8
00:00:43,225 --> 00:00:44,425
Thank you, ma'am.

9
00:02:51,345 --> 00:02:54,465
- I don't know much about that.
- That's the…

10
00:02:55,385 --> 00:02:58,065
- See you guys.
- Bye. See you.

11
00:02:58,145 --> 00:02:59,785
- Okay. Bye.
- See you, Priya.

12
00:02:59,865 --> 00:03:00,785
- Bye.
- Bye.

13
00:03:00,865 --> 00:03:01,905
- There it is.
- Bye.

14
00:03:01,985 --> 00:03:03,705
- Bye.
- See you on the next flight.

15
00:03:15,865 --> 00:03:16,985
Your cab's not coming.

16
00:03:18,745 --> 00:03:20,905
- Excuse me?
- AIU.

17
00:03:22,425 --> 00:03:23,705
Can you come with me for a sec?

18
00:03:26,345 --> 00:03:29,145
Any problem? What happened, sir?

19
00:03:29,225 --> 00:03:32,625
We've received intel that you're
carrying gold concealed on your body.

20
00:03:43,345 --> 00:03:44,705
Don't worry.

21
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:47,985
I know Captain Kapoor
is making you do this.

22
00:03:49,825 --> 00:03:52,705
Please come.
Let's sit comfortably and talk.

23
00:03:56,865 --> 00:03:57,785
Please come.

24
00:04:40,585 --> 00:04:41,705
Why do you do this?

25
00:04:58,305 --> 00:04:59,745
He…

26
00:05:01,865 --> 00:05:02,745
is my fiancé.

27
00:05:03,865 --> 00:05:07,985
We are planning to buy a flat
in Bombay after marriage.

28
00:05:13,305 --> 00:05:16,265
But it isn't possible
with our salaries, so…

29
00:05:25,545 --> 00:05:27,825
That's Rohini Kapoor.

30
00:05:30,585 --> 00:05:35,985
Your fiancé… Captain Shubham Kapoor's
lawfully wedded wife.

31
00:05:37,225 --> 00:05:40,465
She lives with their two kids
and a dog at Mall Road, Delhi.

32
00:05:41,705 --> 00:05:43,185
You're the fourth air hostess

33
00:05:43,265 --> 00:05:46,425
manipulated by Captain Kapoor
with a promise of marriage.

34
00:05:58,705 --> 00:05:59,545
It happens.

35
00:06:00,585 --> 00:06:02,345
Everyone gets screwed over in life.

36
00:06:14,505 --> 00:06:15,745
Bastard!

37
00:06:24,665 --> 00:06:25,665
Now?

38
00:06:25,745 --> 00:06:27,185
I have an offer for you.

39
00:06:28,265 --> 00:06:29,945
Carry on with what you are doing.

40
00:06:31,305 --> 00:06:32,945
I just want to get that bastard.

41
00:06:43,465 --> 00:06:46,705
PRIYA - ALL WELL, HAD DOZED OFF.
UP NOW. WILL SEE YOU SOON.

42
00:06:49,385 --> 00:06:50,225
Done.

43
00:07:32,745 --> 00:07:35,105
- Well, hello.
- Hi.

44
00:07:35,745 --> 00:07:37,465
- Nice.
- Come in.

45
00:07:39,265 --> 00:07:41,505
Blue looks really good on you, yeah.

46
00:07:41,585 --> 00:07:44,905
- Really?
- Oh, really! How I missed you!

47
00:07:44,985 --> 00:07:46,345
Me too!

48
00:07:51,065 --> 00:07:55,025
There are five in here. Hide them well.

49
00:07:56,545 --> 00:07:58,225
Done. I'll be right back.

50
00:08:33,865 --> 00:08:35,305
Wrong timing.

51
00:08:36,505 --> 00:08:39,784
- After three days.
- Damn!

52
00:08:41,904 --> 00:08:45,425
Okay, you rest up. I'll be right back.

53
00:08:45,505 --> 00:08:47,625
Hey, where are you going?

54
00:08:49,024 --> 00:08:50,625
It's Bangkok, baby.

55
00:08:52,425 --> 00:08:53,425
I'll see you.

56
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:01,905
- I'm gonna miss you.
- I'll miss you too.

57
00:09:08,345 --> 00:09:09,465
- See you.
- Bye.

58
00:09:39,425 --> 00:09:40,265
Hello, sir.

59
00:09:53,905 --> 00:09:56,185
Sir, what's wrong? Any problem?

60
00:09:57,585 --> 00:09:58,985
Whose bag is this?

61
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:01,345
Sir, that's my bag. What's the problem?

62
00:10:06,785 --> 00:10:07,905
Come with me, please.

63
00:10:07,985 --> 00:10:11,065
I've been going through this channel
for ten years. I've never been stopped.

64
00:10:11,145 --> 00:10:12,145
What's the problem, sir?

65
00:10:12,225 --> 00:10:13,345
What happened today?

66
00:10:13,425 --> 00:10:14,625
Will you open this, please?

67
00:10:14,705 --> 00:10:16,505
Sir, but can you tell me what's up?

68
00:10:17,265 --> 00:10:18,585
Okay, I'll open it.

69
00:10:18,665 --> 00:10:21,225
Sir, but you won't find a thing.
What are you looking for, sir?

70
00:10:21,305 --> 00:10:23,185
Sir, a pilot's life is very boring.

71
00:10:23,265 --> 00:10:26,065
We only have clothes and toiletries.
Nothing else, sir.

72
00:10:27,145 --> 00:10:29,465
Sir, you won't find anything.
I'm a senior pilot, sir.

73
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:30,865
Why are you checking me?

74
00:10:34,025 --> 00:10:34,905
Sir!

75
00:10:36,185 --> 00:10:39,425
Sir, that's not what it looks like.
Sir, this is not mine.

76
00:10:39,505 --> 00:10:42,585
Sir, I'm being set up. I'm not kidding.
This is not mine, sir.

77
00:10:42,665 --> 00:10:45,465
Sir, people are jealous of me
in the company. I'm not kidding, sir.

78
00:10:45,545 --> 00:10:46,545
These are not mine, sir.

79
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:48,985
I'm a very clean guy, sir. I'm…

80
00:11:04,945 --> 00:11:05,945
Bitch.

81
00:11:14,585 --> 00:11:15,705
Well done.

82
00:11:20,985 --> 00:11:23,385
- Were you scared?
- No.

83
00:11:24,465 --> 00:11:26,385
I knew you had my back.

84
00:11:37,025 --> 00:11:39,025
Coffee's very nice. Isn't it?

85
00:11:48,145 --> 00:11:49,465
The weather has suddenly changed.

86
00:11:49,545 --> 00:11:52,025
You can come to the point, you know?

87
00:11:58,265 --> 00:12:00,945
Priya, a gold smuggling racket
is going on in Al Dera.

88
00:12:01,025 --> 00:12:04,105
We need to infiltrate it. You up for it?

89
00:12:06,145 --> 00:12:07,345
You know I will.

90
00:12:08,785 --> 00:12:11,585
That's why you didn't arrest me, right?

91
00:12:14,345 --> 00:12:16,945
Priya, this is very dangerous.
Think twice.

92
00:12:17,025 --> 00:12:17,985
If you refuse,

93
00:12:18,065 --> 00:12:19,425
I'll understand.

94
00:12:19,505 --> 00:12:22,905
And I promise,
they won't find a clue against you.

95
00:12:22,985 --> 00:12:26,145
But give it a thought again, please.

96
00:12:26,225 --> 00:12:27,105
I don't need to.

97
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:38,425
- I should be grateful.
- To whom?

98
00:12:40,345 --> 00:12:42,465
I should be grateful to Captain Kapoor.

99
00:12:42,545 --> 00:12:44,705
Thanks to him, we have Priya 2.0.

100
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:53,465
Aren't you underestimating yourself?

101
00:13:02,745 --> 00:13:08,465
{\an8}He's the man behind all the gold
that lands in India from Al Dera. Anna.

102
00:13:12,305 --> 00:13:14,745
<i>Anna is treated as god</i>
<i>in the villages of Kerala.</i>

103
00:13:14,825 --> 00:13:17,985
<i>As he has helped</i>
<i>a lot of people get jobs here.</i>

104
00:13:18,065 --> 00:13:22,945
<i>But nobody knows that</i>
<i>through his Manpower Consultancy,</i>

105
00:13:23,025 --> 00:13:27,545
<i>Anna identifies the needy</i>
<i>and makes them his couriers.</i>

106
00:13:32,425 --> 00:13:34,665
<i>This is Anna's right-hand guy, Suresh.</i>

107
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,185
{\an8}And this is Rahul.

108
00:13:38,265 --> 00:13:41,505
<i>Anna's nephew</i>
<i>and our means to infiltrate the gang.</i>

109
00:13:47,225 --> 00:13:48,985
<i>Rahul frequently travels to Mumbai,</i>

110
00:13:49,065 --> 00:13:50,505
<i>and he only flies Emirair.</i>

111
00:13:50,585 --> 00:13:52,785
<i>We get his schedule</i>
<i>from our Advanced Passenger--</i>

112
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:54,385
Wait a sec. Wait a sec.

113
00:13:54,465 --> 00:13:57,745
He flies Emirair,
but I work for Fly Thai Airways.

114
00:13:58,465 --> 00:13:59,305
Not anymore.

115
00:13:59,865 --> 00:14:01,025
Excuse me, sir.

116
00:14:01,705 --> 00:14:04,945
Would you like a complimentary upgrade?
There's a seat available.

117
00:14:05,025 --> 00:14:05,865
Sure.

118
00:14:09,585 --> 00:14:10,665
So, that's your seat.

119
00:14:11,505 --> 00:14:12,865
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

120
00:14:19,945 --> 00:14:21,905
Sir, would you like to have something?

121
00:14:23,665 --> 00:14:24,505
Thank you.

122
00:14:33,265 --> 00:14:35,545
- Hello, sir.
- Oh, hi.

123
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:37,185
Hi. How've you been?

124
00:14:37,265 --> 00:14:38,105
Good.

125
00:14:38,185 --> 00:14:39,185
There's a complimentary--

126
00:14:39,265 --> 00:14:40,305
Upgrade.

127
00:14:45,745 --> 00:14:48,265
- Sir.
- Thank you.

128
00:14:55,305 --> 00:14:56,265
Hi, sir.

129
00:15:00,945 --> 00:15:02,225
- Sir.
- Thank you.

130
00:15:02,305 --> 00:15:03,225
I'll just be back.

131
00:15:03,305 --> 00:15:04,545
Excuse me.

132
00:15:09,065 --> 00:15:12,265
Sorry, sir. But, I'm engaged.

133
00:15:12,345 --> 00:15:14,665
That shouldn't be a problem for a dinner.

134
00:15:14,745 --> 00:15:18,545
Next time you are in Al Dera, call me.
Let me host you this time.

135
00:15:26,305 --> 00:15:27,305
Sure.

136
00:15:31,745 --> 00:15:35,665
Obviously the issue was at our end, right?
We didn't communicate at all. Just a sec.

137
00:15:36,105 --> 00:15:37,345
- Hello?
- Hi.

138
00:15:37,425 --> 00:15:38,345
Hi. Who is this?

139
00:15:38,425 --> 00:15:40,385
This is Priya. Remember me?

140
00:15:41,305 --> 00:15:42,305
Just a sec.

141
00:16:08,425 --> 00:16:11,265
You didn't tell me what exactly do you do?

142
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:13,465
I run a global export business.

143
00:16:13,545 --> 00:16:14,425
Wow!

144
00:16:15,145 --> 00:16:18,465
Nothing great about it.
We're just making some money.

145
00:16:18,545 --> 00:16:22,025
Really? Sounds interesting to me.

146
00:16:26,225 --> 00:16:29,105
Ten kilos of gold strapped to her body.

147
00:16:29,745 --> 00:16:32,545
And she went through the green channel.

148
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:38,385
She had it strapped everywhere
on her body.

149
00:16:38,465 --> 00:16:41,225
You should've seen her face.

150
00:16:41,305 --> 00:16:45,385
Unbelievable! I mean… And you know what?

151
00:16:45,465 --> 00:16:48,665
It was her third trip in six months.

152
00:16:49,225 --> 00:16:51,625
Not a clue about smuggling
and wanted to be a <i>popat.</i>

153
00:16:55,985 --> 00:16:59,625
<i>Popat </i>means… courier.

154
00:17:05,465 --> 00:17:07,705
You know a lot about smuggling.

155
00:17:11,825 --> 00:17:13,385
Not just smuggling,

156
00:17:14,505 --> 00:17:17,305
Mumbai International Airport,
customs officers,

157
00:17:17,385 --> 00:17:20,385
helpers, loaders,

158
00:17:21,105 --> 00:17:22,025
I know about them all.

159
00:17:26,665 --> 00:17:28,665
All those ready to take the plunge,

160
00:17:29,785 --> 00:17:30,745
I know it all.

161
00:17:50,705 --> 00:17:51,545
Priya!

162
00:17:52,665 --> 00:17:53,665
- All okay?
- Sorry.

163
00:17:53,745 --> 00:17:55,585
- It's nothing. No.
- Hey, why are you crying?

164
00:17:56,985 --> 00:17:58,785
They're firing me.

165
00:17:58,865 --> 00:18:00,945
- For unruly behavior.
- What?

166
00:18:01,025 --> 00:18:04,105
Tell me, do you find me unruly?

167
00:18:04,185 --> 00:18:05,625
No, no, not at all.

168
00:18:07,025 --> 00:18:10,825
And ever since Amit heard about this,
he called off the engagement.

169
00:18:13,985 --> 00:18:16,145
Listen, stop crying. Stop crying.

170
00:18:16,705 --> 00:18:19,905
I'm there for you. I'll sort it out.

171
00:18:25,985 --> 00:18:27,665
Trust me, I'll make it all right.

172
00:18:51,545 --> 00:18:54,025
Welcome. May I?

173
00:18:58,465 --> 00:19:00,585
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

174
00:19:08,185 --> 00:19:11,785
Priya, I told you about Anna, right?
This is Anna.

175
00:19:11,865 --> 00:19:14,825
My mom, my dad, my boss. He is my world.

176
00:19:15,385 --> 00:19:16,385
Hello.

177
00:19:17,825 --> 00:19:20,945
And this is the vice-captain of our team,
Suresh <i>kaka.</i>

178
00:19:22,065 --> 00:19:23,065
Priya.

179
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:32,265
- Anna, shall I show her the office?
- Sure, go ahead.

180
00:19:32,985 --> 00:19:33,865
Come.

181
00:19:41,785 --> 00:19:42,865
What happened?

182
00:19:44,705 --> 00:19:45,905
No, nothing.

183
00:21:14,945 --> 00:21:15,865
- Hi.
- Yes, ma'am.

184
00:21:15,945 --> 00:21:18,865
- Which way to the coffee shop? Thanks.
- This way, ma'am.

185
00:22:16,225 --> 00:22:17,545
All good?

186
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:22,865
Yeah. All well.

187
00:22:23,705 --> 00:22:26,145
Two guys have been following me
from the airport.

188
00:22:26,985 --> 00:22:31,225
One is sitting in the lobby trying hard
to read a newspaper and the other one

189
00:22:31,305 --> 00:22:33,185
is smoking in front of the main gate.

190
00:22:33,265 --> 00:22:34,345
Let's go.

191
00:23:18,465 --> 00:23:20,905
I found this list
in a file at Anna's office.

192
00:23:23,105 --> 00:23:26,225
It has the names of those officers
who are confirmed to be working for Anna.

193
00:23:28,545 --> 00:23:32,065
- When did Patel join them?
- It's been three months.

194
00:23:33,505 --> 00:23:37,825
Take a look. Suresh has devised
two new methods of concealing the gold.

195
00:23:38,865 --> 00:23:40,705
First, concealing it in suitcases.

196
00:23:49,465 --> 00:23:53,145
<i>One can carry 5.5 kilos of gold</i>
<i>in check-in bag and 3.5 in a carry-on bag.</i>

197
00:23:53,225 --> 00:23:55,785
These guys are very intelligent.

198
00:23:57,105 --> 00:23:58,265
The second one?

199
00:23:59,705 --> 00:24:01,345
I told you about those chemists.

200
00:24:02,265 --> 00:24:04,385
<i>They have invented a chemical process</i>

201
00:24:04,465 --> 00:24:07,025
<i>by which they</i>
<i>can convert gold bars into powder.</i>

202
00:24:17,145 --> 00:24:19,745
<i>This powder looks exactly like</i>
<i>Oranix powder,</i>

203
00:24:19,825 --> 00:24:22,185
and it can't be detected by scanners.

204
00:24:22,265 --> 00:24:24,985
They bring it here
and convert it back into bars.

205
00:24:26,065 --> 00:24:28,625
I've handed over one-kilo boxes
to five couriers myself.

206
00:24:29,825 --> 00:24:31,265
And they faced no issues.

207
00:24:31,345 --> 00:24:33,625
Is there any talk about new officers?

208
00:24:33,705 --> 00:24:35,465
It's a wait and watch situation.

209
00:24:36,665 --> 00:24:38,905
Anyway, they smuggle goods only when

210
00:24:38,985 --> 00:24:40,345
their officers are on duty.

211
00:24:44,425 --> 00:24:46,705
What is it? What are you thinking?

212
00:24:47,905 --> 00:24:50,625
I'm thinking
how to crack down hard on them.

213
00:24:57,105 --> 00:24:58,025
I have an idea.

214
00:24:59,705 --> 00:25:02,305
But Priya, you will have to leave
Al Dera after that.

215
00:25:03,185 --> 00:25:04,825
If I leave Al Dera,

216
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:07,105
where will I work?

217
00:25:09,905 --> 00:25:11,065
And where will I stay?

218
00:25:12,905 --> 00:25:14,305
Exactly what I was thinking.

219
00:25:15,465 --> 00:25:16,345
Where will you stay?

220
00:25:20,425 --> 00:25:21,545
Okay, when is your flight?

221
00:25:22,465 --> 00:25:24,585
Soon. In two hours.

222
00:26:26,425 --> 00:26:27,625
What's happening here?

223
00:26:28,065 --> 00:26:32,665
- Hey, hurry up! Move away!
- Two minutes. I'm working on it.

224
00:26:32,745 --> 00:26:36,225
What's going on? Sergio, go and check.

225
00:26:46,905 --> 00:26:48,905
Hey, lady! What are you doing, huh?

226
00:28:42,625 --> 00:28:44,985
- It's all yours.
- Good job.

227
00:28:56,385 --> 00:28:57,745
Rob!

228
00:29:01,505 --> 00:29:02,385
Thank you.

229
00:29:29,185 --> 00:29:30,545
- Hello?
<i>- Good morning, sir.</i>

230
00:29:31,105 --> 00:29:32,425
The packet has been secured.

231
00:29:32,505 --> 00:29:33,945
Good. Value?

232
00:29:34,025 --> 00:29:36,985
Four hundred crore plus.
Had to give two to the local gang.

233
00:29:37,065 --> 00:29:39,825
- How long will distribution take?
- Close to three weeks.

234
00:29:40,625 --> 00:29:42,825
I'll send the flight details by tomorrow.

235
00:29:42,905 --> 00:29:43,745
Okay.

236
00:29:59,625 --> 00:30:00,505
Luke.

237
00:30:02,105 --> 00:30:06,665
- Is he the one who committed the theft?
- He wanted to get married. He was in Rome.

238
00:30:18,145 --> 00:30:19,105
Don't kill me.

239
00:30:20,185 --> 00:30:21,185
Please.

240
00:30:22,745 --> 00:30:24,425
Don't kill me.

241
00:30:29,265 --> 00:30:30,265
Please.

242
00:30:33,865 --> 00:30:35,265
Don't kill me.

243
00:30:44,385 --> 00:30:45,585
Come in.

244
00:30:48,945 --> 00:30:50,145
- Sir.
- Arjun.

245
00:30:50,785 --> 00:30:52,665
Come. Take a seat.

246
00:30:56,065 --> 00:30:57,705
I have some good news.

247
00:30:57,785 --> 00:31:01,265
The World Customs Conference is being
held in Mumbai on the 24th of this month.

248
00:31:01,345 --> 00:31:02,785
Good news is that you and your team

249
00:31:02,865 --> 00:31:05,545
will be responsible
for managing the guest protocol.

250
00:31:07,665 --> 00:31:10,025
Sir, you brought us back
to curb smuggling.

251
00:31:10,745 --> 00:31:12,625
If we'll be serving delegates…

252
00:31:18,425 --> 00:31:22,625
Shift details and new roster for officer
duties will reach syndicate by evening.

253
00:31:22,705 --> 00:31:26,465
When they get to know that all former
officers are on duty at the airport,

254
00:31:26,545 --> 00:31:30,585
they will think that the channels
are open for them all day long.

255
00:31:31,185 --> 00:31:32,025
Brilliant.

256
00:31:46,865 --> 00:31:48,145
Yes, sir.

257
00:31:49,705 --> 00:31:52,305
Okay. I'll send it over to you.

258
00:32:17,985 --> 00:32:22,385
- Hey, man! Watch it!
- Oh, Patel sir. Sorry. I was distracted.

259
00:32:22,465 --> 00:32:25,985
- Sorry.
- Congrats on getting reinstated, Meena.

260
00:32:26,785 --> 00:32:29,145
What good is this reinstatement,
Patel sahib?

261
00:32:29,225 --> 00:32:32,305
My entire batch has been assigned
to serve the delegates.

262
00:32:32,385 --> 00:32:37,745
Did we join Customs to catch smugglers
or serve these foreigners?

263
00:32:37,825 --> 00:32:39,065
Yeah.

264
00:32:39,145 --> 00:32:42,865
I saw it in the duty roster.
But why are you complaining?

265
00:32:42,945 --> 00:32:47,145
Have fun in the 5-star hotel for five days
and then you can catch the smugglers.

266
00:32:47,225 --> 00:32:51,705
It's not like smuggling is going to
stop at this airport, right? Shake on it.

267
00:33:00,945 --> 00:33:04,265
I think the piece goes here. Right?

268
00:33:05,745 --> 00:33:07,945
- Nerissa!
- Yes, sir?

269
00:33:10,065 --> 00:33:12,585
Oh, hi!
What are you playing? Can I join you?

270
00:33:12,665 --> 00:33:13,505
Yes, Patel.

271
00:33:13,585 --> 00:33:16,745
- Hello, sir. Good news for you.
<i>- What is it?</i>

272
00:33:17,545 --> 00:33:20,705
Mumbai airport will be ours
for the taking on the 24th.

273
00:33:30,345 --> 00:33:33,025
Who told you about this?

274
00:33:34,065 --> 00:33:37,065
Suresh <i>kaka,</i> have you forgotten,
I used to be an air hostess?

275
00:33:37,865 --> 00:33:39,745
I still have contacts at the airport.

276
00:33:39,825 --> 00:33:43,545
I haven't forgotten anything.
But your proposal is very risky.

277
00:33:44,185 --> 00:33:45,025
Suresh!

278
00:33:53,705 --> 00:33:55,025
Namaskar, Choudhary sahib.

279
00:33:55,105 --> 00:33:57,105
- How are you, Anna?
<i>- All well.</i>

280
00:33:57,185 --> 00:33:59,305
Mumbai airport will be on holiday on 24th.

281
00:33:59,385 --> 00:34:01,225
Get the maximum stuff ready.

282
00:34:01,305 --> 00:34:03,025
Twenty men won't be enough for Junior.

283
00:34:03,105 --> 00:34:05,825
- Send some from Al Dera.
<i>- It will be done, sahib.</i>

284
00:34:05,905 --> 00:34:08,945
I'm sending three watches, worth 50 crore.

285
00:34:09,025 --> 00:34:11,425
They need to reach Mumbai.
How will you do it?

286
00:34:12,545 --> 00:34:15,545
My network of captains
will take care of it, Choudhary sahib.

287
00:34:15,625 --> 00:34:16,625
Great.

288
00:34:16,705 --> 00:34:17,824
Okay, Choudhary sahib.

289
00:34:21,385 --> 00:34:22,705
Satisfied now?

290
00:34:24,865 --> 00:34:26,385
The chick's intel is correct.

291
00:34:42,264 --> 00:34:45,585
So, what's your plan?

292
00:34:55,025 --> 00:34:58,385
First, we will take 20 kilos of gold
on these nine domestic flights.

293
00:34:58,465 --> 00:35:01,465
That's 180 kilos. 320 kilos is left.

294
00:35:05,465 --> 00:35:09,985
Twenty kilos gold for a single person?
It is risky.

295
00:35:10,065 --> 00:35:12,905
Two people can carry ten kilos each
on the domestic flight.

296
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:15,065
Yes.

297
00:35:16,105 --> 00:35:18,345
- How many passengers do you have?
- Sixty-one.

298
00:35:19,065 --> 00:35:21,865
Good. Sixty-one.

299
00:35:21,945 --> 00:35:23,665
I'll manage with 41.

300
00:35:24,225 --> 00:35:26,065
You can assign
the remaining 20 to Ethiopia.

301
00:35:27,425 --> 00:35:30,345
Give me the details and backgrounds
of these 61 passengers.

302
00:35:30,425 --> 00:35:32,825
I'll send the heavily-built ones
to Ethiopia.

303
00:35:32,905 --> 00:35:34,425
And keep the rest for myself.

304
00:35:36,705 --> 00:35:37,785
Fine.

305
00:35:56,745 --> 00:35:58,025
Here's the list.

306
00:36:02,385 --> 00:36:05,505
One passenger can carry nine kilos of gold
using two suitcases.

307
00:36:07,585 --> 00:36:10,865
Thirty-two times nine is 288.

308
00:36:12,705 --> 00:36:15,265
And we haven't even used
the Oranix powder yet.

309
00:36:15,825 --> 00:36:17,305
How much powder do we have?

310
00:36:17,385 --> 00:36:18,585
About 30-32 kilos.

311
00:36:18,665 --> 00:36:20,865
Perfect. That does it.

312
00:36:20,945 --> 00:36:25,545
These passengers will carry a kilo of
Oranix powder alongwith the suitcases.

313
00:36:33,185 --> 00:36:35,145
Great. Let's do this then.

314
00:36:52,865 --> 00:36:56,145
There are 2,500 chips, Vijay bhai.
How will you do it?

315
00:36:56,225 --> 00:36:59,145
Look, madam.
There are 60 instrument boxes.

316
00:36:59,225 --> 00:37:02,065
Apart from that,
we have sound and light SKP boxes.

317
00:37:02,145 --> 00:37:04,785
Everything will fit in those easily.
Don't worry.

318
00:37:04,865 --> 00:37:09,265
We just need somebody to manage the heavy
luggage at the airport counter. That's it.

319
00:37:09,345 --> 00:37:13,105
I'll take care of that. How many people
are there in the bhangra troupe?

320
00:37:13,185 --> 00:37:16,425
Thirty dancers
and eight support staff members.

321
00:37:16,505 --> 00:37:20,425
You'll be able to send 50 luxury suitcases
and 20 high-end purses through them?

322
00:37:20,505 --> 00:37:25,105
Easily, madam. Don't you worry.
Leave it to me.

323
00:37:25,185 --> 00:37:26,225
Okay.

324
00:37:30,425 --> 00:37:33,105
I've taken this huge financial risk
based solely on your trust.

325
00:37:33,185 --> 00:37:37,345
Don't worry, Arbab. The consignment
will land in Mumbai in two days.

326
00:37:37,425 --> 00:37:39,545
The account will be settled within a week.

327
00:37:44,465 --> 00:37:47,225
Yes, we are on time. All right!

328
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:40,145
Blurt out what's bothering you.
Or else it'll keep hurting.

329
00:38:40,225 --> 00:38:45,145
Such a big consignment is being sent
in one go. If something goes haywire…

330
00:38:45,225 --> 00:38:48,025
I spoke to Patel. The intel is solid.

331
00:38:48,105 --> 00:38:50,465
Our men are on duty. There's no risk.

332
00:38:50,545 --> 00:38:52,745
Priya's entry into our business like this

333
00:38:53,825 --> 00:38:55,705
kind of bothers me.

334
00:38:56,665 --> 00:38:58,305
What do you want to do about it?

335
00:39:30,545 --> 00:39:31,625
Good evening, sir.

336
00:39:31,705 --> 00:39:33,025
- Get me a double.
- Sure.

337
00:39:37,905 --> 00:39:39,145
Come over, Arjun.

338
00:39:45,945 --> 00:39:47,065
I just got a tip.

339
00:39:47,145 --> 00:39:51,305
Choudhary Syndicate is planning
to land 500 kilos of yellow on the 24th.

340
00:39:51,385 --> 00:39:53,425
- We have to get them.
- But how?

341
00:39:53,505 --> 00:39:55,865
We are not going to be
on counter duty that day.

342
00:39:55,945 --> 00:40:00,545
That's only on paper. Prakash sir
will change the roster at the last minute.

343
00:40:01,625 --> 00:40:03,105
Okay.

344
00:40:03,185 --> 00:40:06,065
Don't mess with small-time couriers
for the next few days.

345
00:40:06,145 --> 00:40:08,265
I want their confidence to grow.

346
00:40:13,945 --> 00:40:15,625
- Manoj.
- Please come, sir.

347
00:41:26,945 --> 00:41:29,665
- Have you booked your ticket?
- Yes, I'll send you my boarding pass.

348
00:41:29,745 --> 00:41:31,265
Don't worry about me.

349
00:41:31,345 --> 00:41:33,505
Priya, you have to leave

350
00:41:33,585 --> 00:41:36,025
before the first contraband flight
takes off, got it?

351
00:41:36,105 --> 00:41:38,185
I've sent you two lists.

352
00:41:38,265 --> 00:41:40,305
The first list has details of 52 people.

353
00:41:40,385 --> 00:41:42,785
Twenty will come from Ethiopia
and 32 from Al Dera.

354
00:41:42,865 --> 00:41:45,065
The second list
carries names of nine people

355
00:41:45,145 --> 00:41:47,105
and 18 seat numbers
where packets are hidden.

356
00:41:47,185 --> 00:41:49,465
But these nine people
will leave for their destinations

357
00:41:49,545 --> 00:41:51,745
after leaving the packages at their seats.

358
00:41:51,825 --> 00:41:55,025
Then, 18 new couriers will board
those domestic converted flights

359
00:41:55,105 --> 00:41:58,305
and each one of them will carry a package
and exit as soon as the plane lands.

360
00:41:58,385 --> 00:42:01,625
Good. I'll meet you directly in Mumbai.

361
00:42:02,385 --> 00:42:04,625
- You take care.
- I will. Bye.

362
00:42:57,385 --> 00:42:59,745
- Hi.
- Hello, madam.

363
00:42:59,825 --> 00:43:03,825
- Are you going out?
- No. I was thinking of hitting the gym.

364
00:43:03,905 --> 00:43:05,625
You know I haven't gone for three days.

365
00:43:05,705 --> 00:43:08,305
And last night,
I had so many desserts, so--

366
00:43:08,385 --> 00:43:12,345
Forget it. Anna has called
for an urgent meeting. We have to go.

367
00:43:12,905 --> 00:43:16,185
You could've just called me.
I'd have come directly.

368
00:43:16,865 --> 00:43:21,065
But then I would've missed
the chance to go on long drive with you.

369
00:43:22,665 --> 00:43:23,745
Let's go.

370
00:43:23,825 --> 00:43:25,665
Just a sec. I'll get my bag.

371
00:43:48,145 --> 00:43:49,185
Shall we?

372
00:43:51,465 --> 00:43:52,545
Let's go.

373
00:43:58,105 --> 00:44:00,865
Anna and Choudhary sahib
are very happy with your work.

374
00:44:02,825 --> 00:44:05,145
Anna was saying
that a big bonus awaits you this time.

375
00:44:09,785 --> 00:44:11,465
- Can I ask you something?
- Yes.

376
00:44:12,665 --> 00:44:15,225
International flights
are converted to domestic flights,

377
00:44:16,465 --> 00:44:19,385
was this your own idea
or somebody else told you?

378
00:44:20,705 --> 00:44:22,105
Who will tell me, Rahul?

379
00:44:25,225 --> 00:44:27,545
Some customs officer might have told you.

380
00:44:33,545 --> 00:44:36,145
You think I work for Customs?

381
00:44:39,385 --> 00:44:42,665
Not me, Suresh <i>kaka</i> thinks so.

382
00:44:43,785 --> 00:44:45,745
That's why he's
given me the responsibility

383
00:44:45,825 --> 00:44:48,425
of keeping an eye on you
till the consignment lands.

384
00:45:06,105 --> 00:45:07,665
Don't open the door.

385
00:45:11,665 --> 00:45:12,665
Yes, Rahul. Tell me.

386
00:45:12,745 --> 00:45:14,665
Hello, Anna. Cops have surrounded us.

387
00:45:14,745 --> 00:45:16,905
- What? Why?
- I don't know.

388
00:45:27,905 --> 00:45:30,025
- Come out of the car.
- Come out of the car, madam

389
00:45:30,105 --> 00:45:31,425
Why you stop me, officer?

390
00:45:31,505 --> 00:45:32,905
Hello, Rahul?

391
00:45:33,425 --> 00:45:36,225
Step out of the car, quickly!

392
00:45:38,025 --> 00:45:39,145
Come out.

393
00:45:39,225 --> 00:45:40,465
Come out of the car!

394
00:45:40,545 --> 00:45:41,385
Stop right here.

395
00:45:43,705 --> 00:45:46,185
Move faster, move.

396
00:45:48,585 --> 00:45:50,185
Check the car.

397
00:45:54,105 --> 00:45:57,065
What do you want? Why have you stopped us?

398
00:46:02,585 --> 00:46:03,985
This is not ours.

399
00:46:04,065 --> 00:46:06,025
- Sir, sir. This is not my car, sir.
- Officer!

400
00:46:06,105 --> 00:46:08,145
Carry her out. Take it with you.

401
00:46:08,225 --> 00:46:09,785
There is a misunderstanding, Officer.

402
00:46:09,865 --> 00:46:12,105
- Rahul, tell them! This is not my car!
- Take her with you and take him away.

403
00:46:12,185 --> 00:46:15,825
- Take her with you, and take him away.
- Please try to understand, officer!

404
00:46:15,905 --> 00:46:17,825
Please try to understand.
This is not ours.

405
00:46:17,905 --> 00:46:19,225
Get in the car!

406
00:46:19,305 --> 00:46:22,345
- Let me make a call. Let me…
- We will talk, get in the car.

407
00:46:24,025 --> 00:46:24,865
Rahul.

408
00:46:24,945 --> 00:46:27,985
There is a misunderstanding.
Will somebody listen to me?

409
00:46:28,065 --> 00:46:30,865
Please let me…

410
00:50:30,425 --> 00:50:35,425
Subtitle translation by: Sanjay Malhotra
